<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1525] HTable.incrementColumnValue hangs() </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1525</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the following code, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   @Test&lt;br/&gt;
    public void usingIncrement() throws Exception &lt;br/&gt;
    {&lt;br/&gt;
        long siteId = 1234;&lt;br/&gt;
        long publisherId = 5678;&lt;br/&gt;
        Date eventTime = DATE_INPUT_FORMAT.parse(&quot;2009-06-15 13:08:54&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        long[] metrics = new long[] &lt;/p&gt;
{ 10, 22, 32 }
&lt;p&gt;;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        byte[] rowKey = Bytes.toBytes(siteId + &quot;_&quot; + ROW_KEY_FORMAT.format(eventTime));&lt;br/&gt;
        byte[] family = Bytes.toBytes(FAMILY_PUBLISHER);&lt;br/&gt;
        byte[] qualifier = Bytes.toBytes(publisherId);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        HTable table = getTable();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        for (int i1 = 0, n1 = metrics.length; n1 &amp;gt; 0; i1++, n1--) {&lt;br/&gt;
            LOGGER.info(&quot;processing [&lt;/p&gt;
{0}] ...&quot;, i1);&lt;br/&gt;
            table.incrementColumnValue(rowKey, family, qualifier, metrics&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;i1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;);&lt;br/&gt;
            LOGGER.info(&quot;processing [{0}
&lt;p&gt;] completed&quot;, i1);&lt;br/&gt;
        }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        table.close();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        queryMetrics(table, siteId, publisherId, eventTime);&lt;br/&gt;
    }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The call table.incrementColumnValue hangs. Have to kill the hbase client and the master processes to get around the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;ubuntu 9.04&lt;br/&gt;
jdk 1.6.0.13&lt;br/&gt;
hadoop 0.20.0&lt;br/&gt;
hbase 0.20.0-dev &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;trunk&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
