                            <comment id="12719723" author="irfanmohammed" created="Mon, 15 Jun 2009 19:21:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached the client and the master thread dumps.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12719725" author="irfanmohammed" created="Mon, 15 Jun 2009 19:22:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Check for the non-null condition in the finally block when releasing the rowLock.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12719727" author="irfanmohammed" created="Mon, 15 Jun 2009 19:24:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;check for the non-null in the finally block before releasing the row lock.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12719733" author="apparition" created="Mon, 15 Jun 2009 19:40:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ah.. yeah... good find!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12719745" author="ryanobjc" created="Mon, 15 Jun 2009 20:06:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like the row lock is being acquired and never released.  Refactoring lossage probably.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is a slightly revised patch (use -p1) to always release the row lock.  There is some confusion because most of the other functions are like so:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public void doSomething(..., Integer lockid) &lt;/p&gt;
{

// stuff

}
&lt;p&gt; finally &lt;/p&gt;
{
  if (lockid == null)
     releaseLock(lid);
}
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this looks weird, but what is really happening is we are unlocking the rowlock if we are &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; passed a row lock (lockid == null), otherwise we leave the row locked and trust our caller to unlock it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12719747" author="stack" created="Mon, 15 Jun 2009 20:08:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12719750" author="ryanobjc" created="Mon, 15 Jun 2009 20:18:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks for the bug report!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
